Description:
Oversized Apartment Awash with Sunshine
Savour the convenience and low maintenance lifestyle on offer at this superb oversized apartment in leafy Kensington Road. This tremendously spacious north facing home offers an expansive living space with floor to ceiling windows and a balcony, a generous sunny bedroom with mirrored built in robes, a modern kitchen with granite bench tops, quality stainless steel appliances and a dishwasher plus a large bathroom with shower over bath. Complete with off street parking and showcasing timber floorboards throughout, washing machine facilities, security intercom entrance, ceiling fans, panel heating, an elevated position and swathes of glorious northern light. A stroll to parks plus Toorak Road shops, cafes, restaurants and trams, all within easy access of Toorak Village, Chapel Street and South Yarra Station.

Description:
Granada Mews Penthouse
A unique South Yarra oasis, this brilliantly refurbished garden penthouse in the evocative c1930's Howard Lawson designed "Granada Court" delivers the ultimate riverside lifestyle walking distance to the Botanic Gardens, MCG, sports precinct, Toorak Rd's shops and restaurants and good schools.
Enjoying its own private entrance, the light-filled interior spaces feature Spotted Gum floors throughout. The beautiful main bedroom with bay window and a second double bedroom offering Yarra River views share a stylish bathroom. The generous living room with bay window is warmed by a rustic wood stove heater. The sleek gourmet kitchen boasting stone benches and European appliances and an expansive dining area open to a spectacular lush and entirely private landscaped garden sanctuary with water feature, fire pit and stunning pergola covered entertaining terrace with built in seating.
The only residence in Granada with a garage (smart phone remote), this irresistible domain also includes video intercom, Euro-laundry, storage and ducted heating and cooling.
Insights: 1/65 Alexandra Avenue, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2020 and 233 other 2 bedroom unit in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Freestanding 5 Bedroom Residence In The Domain
Stunning contemporary double storey residence superbly renovated throughout in this highly sought after Botanic Gardens precinct. Inner city living at it's best and scope to rebuild STCA.

Description:
Refined style, single level excellence
Sleek contemporary design and tranquil outdoor spaces define the appeal of this stylish single level town residence. Ideally positioned within South Yarra, natural light has been maximised throughout the home thanks to desirable northern orientation at the rear and several serene courtyards. An expansive open plan living area at the rear is enhanced by a gas fireplace and polished concrete floors, opening out to a sizeable private rear deck with green surrounds, providing a superb area for alfresco dining and entertaining. The kitchen showcases an island benchtop and quality appliances including gas cooktop, oven and dishwasher. All three bedrooms feature built in robes, including a sophisticated ensuite main with rain shower. A second chic bathroom, laundry, security system and off street parking for two cars complete the home. Positioned within easy walking distance of Chapel Street and Toorak Road shops and cafes, Hawksburn Village and Hawksburn train station.

Description:
River Views from an Iconic Art Deco
Grand period splendour, abundant natural light plus Yarra River and city skyline views immediately appeal in this charismatic Art Deco apartment situated within the illustrious Beverley Hills complex designed and built by renowned architect Howard Lawson. Opposite Darling Gardens and set amidst a stunning Hollywood-style milieu, the resident facilities boast a pool with grotto and bridge. An elevated position provides total privacy, leafy outlooks and impressive vistas across the city and neighbourhood. Remarkably spacious throughout, refurbishments over the years have promoted this classic apartment into the modern realm, whilst still maintaining all the charm of its time with leadlight windows, decorative cornices and ornate ceiling roses. A gourmet kitchen features European appliances including SMEG five burner cooktop, AEG oven and Bosch DW, the expansive lounge room is sumptuously warmed by the gas log fireplace and a cosy dining nook enjoys a treed outlook. The master bedroom is fitted with built in robes and reverse cycle heating/cooling and opens to a gorgeous balcony, perfect for your morning coffee. An additional bedroom is a rarity in many apartments of this era and the central bathroom with corner spa bath is an added bonus. Inclusions such as laundry facilities and available off street parking upon application are sure to impress as is the convenient locale with Toorak Road shops, trams, restaurants, cafes, amenities and South Yarra Station at one end of the street and the Yarra River cycling trail and buses at the other. Royal Botanic Gardens and popular Lawson Grove Shop are mere moments away.
Insights: 19/61 Darling Street, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2020 and 233 other 2 bedroom unit in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Positioned for convenience in sought after tree-lined Caroline Street, seconds from Toorak Road cafes, restaurants, trams and South Yarra Station, this striking elevated apartment at the rear of a boutique block enjoys a westerly aspect flooding the home with natural light. Description:
'Caslake House'
CASLAKE HOUSE reflects the architectural artistry for which homes by Marcus Martin remain so instantly recognizable, so widely regarded and so highly sought after. Martin's confidence to adopt a style based on restraint and subtlety has been complemented throughout this landmark residence by the light yet comprehensive approach taken to renovation by renowned Melbourne architects Powell & Glenn - with evident, exceptional success. The care taken to preserve the integrity of the home's original elements while entirely updating its inviting spaces creates a mood that's at once classical and contemporary, simultaneously refined yet relaxed. Fabulous formal rooms for living, dining and entertaining, a study and brilliant dimensions for everyday family life are arranged around a central kitchen featuring first class finishes, bespoke Peter Cole benches and a huge walk-in pantry. Four welcoming, luxurious bedrooms, one currently configured as a superb studio, are accompanied on the upstairs level by two beautiful bathrooms and a pair of brilliant balconies, further enhancing the allure of a home that's surrounded by gardens where landscape designer Kate Seddon's sublime skill ensures peace, privacy and perfection. Double garaging completes a memorable Martin property - and enhances an unforgettable Melbourne home - moments from the Royal Botanic Gardens, elite private schools, Toorak Road restaurants, tram routes, the Yarra River and bike tracks to the city.
Insights: 20 Mona Place, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2020 and 21 other 4 bedroom house in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Description:
Premium Address, Filled with Light in a Lifestyle Location
Positioned to satisfy all your cosmopolitan, South Yarra, lifestyle aspirations, while offering easy city commuting, this bright, single bedroom apartment is impressively sized by the standards of one bedroom homes and set within the attractive, older-style 'Oxford' building. Well-presented and comfortable for you to occupy or lease, the home also offers first home buyers and market-savvy investors the opportunity to introduce some of your own style to really reap some rewards. Accessed securely via intercom entry, the home highlights a functionally designed kitchen / meals that also offers an exciting opportunity for easy cosmetic rejuvenation, whilst the lounge / dining is large and light-filled with appealing balcony access. The bedroom, too, enjoys balcony access and large built-in robes, plus there is a bathroom with laundry facilities that is all separate to the wc. A gentle stroll sees you in the heart of Toorak Rd's renowned cafe scene, fine dining and strip shopping, while the intersection with Chapel St sees your lifestyle options grow exponentially. Conveniently, the Number 8 tram is right at your doorstep and Hawksburn Railway Station is comfortably walkable to ensure city access has never been easier, plus you have Hawksburn Village nearby for a more refined cafe culture and Como Park around the corner for some outdoor recreation.
